;; 1. Based on: 107 ;; 2. Description: ;; all estimation methods we can think of ;; 3. Label: ;; ;; 4. Structural model: ;; 5. Covariate model: ;; 6. Inter-individual variability: ;; 7. Inter-occasion variability: ;; 8. Residual variability: ;; 9. Estimation:
$PROBLEM PK model 1 cmt base
$INPUT ID TIME MDV EVID DV AMT SEX WT ETN $DATA acop.csv IGNORE=@ $SUBROUTINES ADVAN2 TRANS2
$PK ET=1 IF(ETN.EQ.3) ET=1.3 KA = THETA(1) CL = THETA(2)*((WT/70)**THETA(6))*( THETA(7)**SEX) * EXP(ETA(1)) V = THETA(3)*EXP(ETA(2)) SC=V
$THETA 2.3 ; KA ; 1/h ; LIN ; Absorption Rate Constant 80.1 ; CL ; L/h ; LIN ; Clearance 500 ; V2 ; L ; LIN ; Volume of Distribution 0 FIX ; RUVp ; ; LIN ; Proportional Error 4.12 ; RUVa ; ng/mL ; LIN ; Additive Error 0.75 ; CL-WT ; ; LIN ; Power Scalar CL-WT 0.559 ; CL-SEX ; ; LIN ; Female CL Change
$OMEGA 0.123188 ; iiv CL 0.1537040 ; iiv V2
$SIGMA 1 FIX
$ERROR IPRED = F IRES = DV-IPRED W = IPRED*THETA(4) + THETA(5) IF (W.EQ.0) W = 1 IWRES = IRES/W Y= IPRED+W*ERR(1)
$EST METHOD=0 MAXEVAL=9999 SIG=3 PRINT=5 NOABORT POSTHOC $EST METHOD=1 INTER MAXEVAL=9999 SIG=3 PRINT=5 NOABORT POSTHOC $EST METHOD=1 INTER MAXEVAL=9999 SIG=3 PRINT=5 NOABORT POSTHOC LAPLACE $EST METHOD=SAEM NBURN=500 NITER=500 CTYPE=0 PRINT=100 $EST METHOD=ITS INTER MAXEVAL=9999 SIG=3 PRINT=5 NOABORT POSTHOC $EST METHOD=BAYES NBURN=1000 NITER=1000 CTYPE=0 PRINT=100 $EST METHOD=IMP INTER EONLY=0 NITER=5 ISAMPLE=3000 PRINT=1 SIGL=8 NOPRIOR=0 $EST METHOD=IMP INTER EONLY=1 NITER=5 ISAMPLE=3000 PRINT=1 SIGL=8 NOPRIOR=1 $ESTIMATION METHOD=IMPMAP NITER=300 ISAMPLE=300 $EST METHOD=IMP INTER EONLY=1 NITER=5 ISAMPLE=3000 PRINT=1 SIGL=8 NOPRIOR=1
$COV PRINT=E UNCONDITIONAL
$TABLE ID TIME DV MDV EVID IPRED IWRES CWRES ONEHEADER NOPRINT FILE=sdtab108 $TABLE ID CL V ONEHEADER NOPRINT FILE=patab108 $TABLE ID SEX ETN ONEHEADER NOPRINT FILE=catab108 $TABLE ID WT ONEHEADER NOPRINT FILE=cotab108
